{"title_page": "Ben Barkow", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{BLP sources|date=September 2009}}\n'''Ben Barkow''' (born 1956) is a writer and was the director of The Wiener Holocaust Library from 1998 to 2019.\n\nBarkow was born in [[Berlin]] but lived in London from the age of four.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.timeout.com/london/attractions/inside-the-london-holocaust-library|title=Inside the London Holocaust library|last=Watts|first=Peter|date=7 May 2008|work=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]]|location = London|accessdate=7 September 2009}}</ref> He studied at the [[Middlesex Polytechnic]] and at [[University College London]].  After employment as a researcher at the [[Wellcome Institute]] for the History of Medicine, he started to work for the Wiener Library Institute of Contemporary History and is today its director.  He is a member of the editorial advisory board of ''[[Jewish Renaissance]]'' magazine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jewishrenaissance.org.uk/about-us/who-we-are.html/|title=Who We Are|publisher=[[Jewish Renaissance]]|accessdate=21 November 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010150551/http://www.jewishrenaissance.org.uk/about-us/who-we-are.html|archive-date=10 October 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Publications ==\nBarkow is the author or editor of these books:\n* ''Alfred Wiener and the Making of the Holocaust Library'' (1997) ({{ISBN|0-85303-328-5}})\n*  ''Testaments of the Holocaust, series 1 \u2013 3'' (editor) (1998\u20132000)\n* ''Philipp Manes, Als ob\u2019s ein Leben w\u00e4r: Tatsachenbericht Theresienstadt 1942-1944'' (editor with Klaus Leist) (2005)\n* ''Novemberpogrom 1938: Die Augenzeugenberichte der Wiener Library'', (with Raphel Gross and Michael Lenarz) London (2008)\n* ''Philipp Manes, As Though it were a Life'' (with Klaus Leist, in preparation)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.wienerlibrary.co.uk/ The Wiener Holocaust Library website]\n*{{Cite news|url=http://www.timeout.com/london/museums-attractions/features/4766/Inside_the_London_Holocaust_library.html#articleAfterMpu|title=Inside the London Holocaust library|last=Watts|first=Peter|date=7 May 2008|work=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]]|location= London|accessdate=7 September 2009}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Barkow, Ben}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Middlesex University]]\n[[Category:Alumni of University College London]]\n[[Category:British non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:British librarians]]\n[[Category:1956 births]]\n[[Category:British male writers]]\n[[Category:Wiener Library]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{BLP sources|date=September 2009}}\n'''Ben Barkow''' (born 1956) is a writer and was the director of The Wiener Holocaust Library from 1998 to 2019.\n\nBarkow was born in [[Berlin]] but lived in London from the age of four.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.timeout.com/london/museums-attractions/features/4766/Inside_the_London_Holocaust_library.html#articleAfterMpu|title=Inside the London Holocaust library|last=Watts|first=Peter|date=7 May 2008|work=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]]|location = London|accessdate=7 September 2009}}</ref> He studied at the [[Middlesex Polytechnic]] and at [[University College London]].  After employment as a researcher at the [[Wellcome Institute]] for the History of Medicine, he started to work for the Wiener Library Institute of Contemporary History and is today its director.  He is a member of the editorial advisory board of ''[[Jewish Renaissance]]'' magazine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jewishrenaissance.org.uk/about-us/who-we-are.html/|title=Who We Are|publisher=[[Jewish Renaissance]]|accessdate=21 November 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010150551/http://www.jewishrenaissance.org.uk/about-us/who-we-are.html|archive-date=10 October 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Publications ==\nBarkow is the author or editor of these books:\n* ''Alfred Wiener a